text.datatype 45.1 (31.10.00)
 - completly rewritten
 - now supports marking
 - now supports searching.
   To open the requester press 'Return'. To search forward press 'Tab' and to
   search backwards press the 'Shift Tab' keys.

text.datatype 45.2 (04.11.00)
 - had problems with CR+LF text files. Fixed.
 - fixed marking problems
 - bottom line wasn't erased when scrolled.
 - uses now a slightly differnt library initialisation code
   great thanks to Olaf and Thor
 - auto copy, thanks to Allan for the framework
 - search can now be case sensitive

text.datatype 45.3 (05.11.00)
 - the right of a line wasn't erased. Fixed.

text.datatype 45.4 (10.11.00)
 - it was always the first line displayed at start. Fixed.

text.datatype 45.5 (17.11.00)
 - the last line at a end of a text wasn't erased. Fixed.

text.datatype 45.6 (18.11.00)
 - when pressing tab in the search requester the string gadget
   gets only deactivated, so the other option can be reached
   with keyboard only

text.datatype 45.7 (23.11.00)
 - there was still a last line problem...

text.datatype 45.8 (28.11.00)
 - fixed an enforcer hit which happened if you word marked a passage below
   the text

-- OS3.9 Release

text.datatype 45.9 (10.12.00)
 - somebody seems to set si->si_HorizUnit without using SetAttrs(), added a workaround
   for this

text.datatype 45.10 (27.02.01)
 - now can search for multiple words on a line

text.datatype 45.11 (04.03.01)
 - returns now STM_SEARCH, STM_SEARCH_NEXT, STM_SEARCH_PREV as trigger methods

text.datatype 45.12 (15.03.01)
 - Pressing Shift B in the search requester exited the string gadget. Fixed.

text.datatype 45.13 (01.07.01)
 - not always scrolled to the left when using the mouse
 - when being layouted all inputs are ignored now

text.datatype 45.14 (06.09.01)
 - fixed printing bug
